The Kaduna State Ministry of Environment and Natural Resources on Saturday partnered with a private company, Cape Gate Nigeria, to sensitise the residents to environment cleanliness. The News Agency of Nigeria(NAN) reports that the company’s employees and those of the Kaduna Environmental Protection Authority and the ministry walked up to seven kilometres, picking up plastic and tyres in the state capital. The walk kick-started a campaign tagged: “Say No to Plastic. Kaduna residents tasked on environmental sanitation How waste turned to gold in Kaduna No to Environmental Sanitation Day